==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metamorphose
<hw>Met`a*mor"phose</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Metamorphosed</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Metamorphosing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧tamorphoser</ets>.]</ety> <def>To change into a different
form; to transform; to transmute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And earth was <qex>metamorphosed</qex> into man.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metamorphose</ent>⟦br⟧

